#: features.js:930
msgid "The Pomodoro technique 🍅"
msgstr "Pomodoro tehnika 🍅"

#: features.js:932
msgid ""
"In the late 1980s, university student Francesco Cirillo couldn't focus on "
"his studies. He bet himself he could stay concentrated for just a few "
"minutes and reached for the first timer he could find — a kitchen one shaped "
"like a tomato. In Italian, a tomato is a “pomodoro”, and that's how the "
"method got its name."
msgstr ""
"Krajem 1980-ih student Francesco Cirillo nije se mogao usredotočiti na "
"studij. Okladio se sam sa sobom da može ostati usredotočen barem nekoliko "
"minuta i zgrabio prvi mjerač vremena koji je našao — kuhinjski, u obliku "
"rajčice. Na talijanskom rajčica je „pomodoro“ — i tako je metoda dobila ime."

#: features.js:933
msgid ""
"The idea is simple: big tasks feel daunting, but a single pomodoro doesn't. "
"Promise yourself just 25 minutes of focus on one task, and starting becomes "
"easy."
msgstr ""
"Ideja je jednostavna: veliki zadaci djeluju zastrašujuće, ali jedan pomodoro "
"ne. Obećaj si samo 25 minuta usredotočenosti na jedan zadatak i početak "
"postaje lak."

#: features.js:934
msgid ""
"The classic rhythm:\n"
"• About 25 minutes — one task, nothing else.\n"
"• A 5-minute breather — step away from the screen.\n"
"• After four pomodoros, take a longer 15–30 minute break."
msgstr ""
"Klasični ritam:\n"
"• Otprilike 25 minuta — samo jedan zadatak, ništa drugo.\n"
"• Petominutni predah — odmakni se od ekrana.\n"
"• Nakon četiri pomodora uzmi dulju pauzu od 15–30 minuta."

#: features.js:935
msgid ""
"This is a starting point, not a rule — the applet lets you change any "
"interval and save your own presets."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je polazišna točka, a ne pravilo — aplet ti omogućuje promjenu svakog "
"intervala i spremanje vlastitih postavki."

#: features.js:936
msgid ""
"And it's not just a productivity fad: the exact numbers are flexible, but "
"the principles behind them are backed by attention research. Staying on one "
"task without switching saves energy — getting back on track after an "
"interruption takes about 23 minutes on average. And regular pauses help you "
"hold focus for longer without burning out."
msgstr ""
"I nije riječ samo o pomodnom triku za produktivnost: točni su brojevi "
"fleksibilni, ali načela iza njih potvrđuju istraživanja pažnje. Ostanak na "
"jednom zadatku bez prebacivanja štedi energiju — nakon prekida za povratak "
"je u prosjeku potrebno oko 23 minute. A redovite stanke pomažu ti dulje "
"zadržati koncentraciju bez izgaranja."

#: features.js:937
msgid ""
"Tip: when something distracts you, don't drop what you're doing — jot the "
"thought down and come back to it on your break. Every finished pomodoro is a "
"small win that keeps your momentum going."
msgstr ""
"Savjet: kad te nešto omete, nemoj odustati od onoga što radiš — zapiši misao "
"i vrati joj se tijekom stanke. Svaki dovršeni pomodoro mala je pobjeda koja "
"održava tvoj zamah."

